  "datePublished": "2026-01-01",
  "description": "The arithmetic mean of a collection of values is their sum divided by their count: given values x1,x2,…,xnx_1, x_2, \\ldots, x_n, the mean is xˉ=(x1+x2+⋯+xn)/n\\bar{x} = (x_1 + x_2 + \\cdots + x_n) / n. If five students score 70, 80, 85, 90, and 100 on a test, the mean is (70+80+85+90+100)/5=85(70 + 80 + 85 + 90 + 100) / 5 = 85. The mean answers \u0026ldquo;what is the typical value?\u0026rdquo; by giving every observation equal weight — each score pulls the mean toward itself by the same amount per unit.\n",
